# Production build config. Vite loads this for `vite build` (production mode),
# overriding the localhost values in `.env` (which are for `vite dev` only).
# Without this file the prod bundle shipped localhost URLs and BOTH login paths
# (Windy SSO + email/password) + the Matrix connection pointed at the user's own
# machine → ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED → nobody could sign in. env.ts already defaults
# to these, but the dev .env was overriding them at build time.
VITE_ACCOUNT_SERVER_URL=https://account.windyword.ai
VITE_MATRIX_HOMESERVER=https://chat.windychat.ai
VITE_WINDY_MAIL_URL=https://app.windymail.ai
